{
  "doc_id": "16649",
  "text": "Unexpectedly, ß4 integrin-deficient keratinocytes could spread more efficiently than DN keratinocytes, as shown in Figure 2A , although cell adhesion and migration on laminin-332 was comparable ( Figures 2B and 2C ). ß4 integrin-deficient keratinocytes express an a3ß1 integrin, which is another laminin-332 receptor. As many groups have previously reported [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , a6ß4 integrin affects a3ß1 integrin function in cell spreading and migration. Therefore, the effects of laminin-332 on cell functions in ß4 integrin-deficient keratinocytes might have opened an alternative pathway that depends on a3ß1 integrin.",
